          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EN-RSL"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The thickness of the entrance Mo foil was",
                "measured using Rutherford backscattering spectrometry",
                "at Hope College and was determined to be 1.93(12)",
                "mg/cm2, introducing an uncertainty of ~40 keV/nucleon",
                "in the beam energy. Additional uncertainty associated",
                "with Eeff includes the energy straggling of the beam",
                "as it traverses through the Mo foil (~2%) and the",
                "hydrogen gas (~1%) and the uncertainty of the beam",
                "energy delivered in ReA (~1%). The uneven energy",
                "straggling distribution from SRIM led to asymmetric",
                "uncertainty in the effective energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR",
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Summing NaI(Tl) (SuN) detector. The",
                "Scintillating Cosmic Ray Eliminating ENsemble",
                " (SuNSCREEN), an array of nine plastic scintillator",
                "bars arranged in a roof-like configuration above SuN."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target was a 4-cm-long gas cell made of plastic",
                "positioned at the center of the SuN detector. It had",
                "a 2-microm-thick molybdenum (Mo) entrance window, a 5-",
                "microm-thick exit window, and was filled with",
                "hydrogen gas at a pressure of ~600 Torr."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A radioactive 73As beam was produced from a source",
                "sample evaporated in the batch-mode ion source. The",
                "beam was accelerated to 3.1 and 3.7 MeV,nucleon (lab.",
                "system) in the ReA reaccelerator facility, and",
                "delivered onto a hydrogen gas-cell target in the",
                "experimental end station. The gamma rays produced by",
                "the reaction were detected using the Summing NaI(Tl)",
                " (SuN) detector and were analyzed using the gamma-",
                "summing technique. Proton capture on the 73As beam",
                "forms a 74Se compound nucleus at an excited state.",
                "Adding all gamma rays originating from a single",
                "cascade forms the so-called \"sum peak\" in the total",
                "absorption spectrum (TAS). The integral of the sum",
                "peak corresponds to the number of reactions detected,",
                "which represents the ratio of the number of reactions",
                "taking place and the number of projectiles impinging",
                "on the target, namely, the experimental yield, Y. The",
                "sum peak had background contributions from two main",
                "sources: cosmic-ray background and beam-induced",
                "background. For the former, the Scintillating Cosmic",
                "Ray Eliminating ENsemble (SuNSCREEN), an array of",
                "nine plastic scintillator bars arranged in a",
                "roof-like configuration above SuN, was utilized as a",
                "veto detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
